DISTURBANCE ERUPTS IN CHULA VISTA JAIL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A disturbance was reported at the San Diego County Jail in Chula Vista about 9 
p.m. Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
Four patients were taken to Scripps Memorial Hospital in Chula Vista with minor 
injuries, said paramedic spokesman Tim Robinson of Hartson Medical Services. 
</P>
<P>
Details from the Sheriff's Department were sketchy, but a sheriff's spokesman 
said the disturbance occurred in Module 4B. The module was locked down, and 
inmates were confined to their cells by 9:23 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
A laundry-room fire was also reported Sunday at the County Jail in El Cajon. 
The fire was extinguished, and no injuries were reported. 
