<TEXT>
<P>
"When people tell me I'm crazy, I say, 'Me crazy? You know what I think is 
crazy? I think bowling is crazy -- taking a ball and rolling it down the floor. 
</P>
<P>
That's crazy. Exploring the mind is not crazy.' " -- Alan Abel, noted hoaxer 
and film maker, in the New Yorker. 
