<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: MUSIC 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BETH KLEID, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Quiet, Please!: It's a conductor's nightmare: The orchestra is in the middle of 
a moving passage when suddenly, a member of the audience lets out a hacking 
cough. 
</P>
<P>
According to conductors at 21 orchestras surveyed by the Warner-Lambert Co. 
about noisy disturbances during performances, it happens too often. Nineteen of 
the 23 conductors who answered the survey said they have been distracted by 
audience noises while conducting. Coughers are the worst, they said. Talking 
and yammering youngsters were problems No. 2 and 3 on the most distracting 
sounds listed in the survey completed last week. BETH KLEID 
</P>
</TEXT>
