<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: MOVIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BETH KLEID, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Rocky Fans Line Up in Philly: The thousands queued up outside the Philadelphia 
Civic Center last Thursday were waiting for tickets to a big fight. Not for 
Tyson, but for Rocky. 
</P>
<P>
Fans slept outside the center hoping to get a ticket to the fight scene in 
"Rocky V." Within about an hour, people had grabbed up 16,000 of the 20,000 
tickets for two days of filming in Sylvester Stallone's latest installment of 
the Rocky Balboa saga. For each day of filming, Thursday and Friday, an 
audience of 10,000 is needed. Dave Fulton, the film's publicist, has refused to 
say who would fight in the movie's final scene. The movie is scheduled for 
release in November by United Artists Pictures Inc. BETH KLEID 
</P>
</TEXT>
