<HEADLINE>
<P>
NIBBLES AND BITS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by Kenneth Williams 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Santa Ana's Way Off Broadway Theater, a basement troupe going into its third 
year, has announced six plays for its 1990 season: "Women of Manhattan" by John 
Patrick Shanley (Feb. 14-March 10); "A Higher Source . . . " by Allison Gappa 
(April 5-29); "Hunting Cockroaches" by Janusz Glowacki (June 7-30); the 
tentatively titled "A State of Mind," an audience-participation drama, also by 
Gappa (Aug. 2-Sept. 2); "Countess Dracula" by Neal DuBrock (Oct. 11-31), and 
"Oh, Fudge" by Monk Ferris (Dec. 6-Jan. 6, 1991). Information: (714) 547-8997. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
