<HEADLINE>
<P>
LOCAL; 
</P>
<P>
MAN KILLS WIFE, THEN HIMSELF 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A man shot and killed his wife early today in their mid-city apartment, 
reported the slaying to police and then fatally shot himself, police said. 
</P>
<P>
Neither the man nor the woman who died in the incident after midnight were 
immediately identified, pending notification of their relatives. Both were 
believed to be in their 50s. 
</P>
<P>
The man called the 911 emergency line about 12:40 a.m., saying he had shot his 
wife and was going to kill himself. He then hung up. Police and paramedics sent 
to the apartment at 716 S. Harvard Blvd. found the two bodies. No motive for 
the murder-suicide had been determined, police said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Brief; Wire 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
