<P>
MISSING ANCHORS RESIGN TV JOBS; 
</P>
<P>
DIRECTOR JUST SAYS NO TO SEQUELS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Service Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
DALTON, Ga. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Jeff Burr is ready to go back to directing his own films, saying he's 
discovered the frustrations of working on sequels after directing "The 
Stepfather II" and "Leatherface: Texas Chainsaw Massacre III." 
</P>
<P>
"I've discovered that I just don't have the mental stability or the temperament 
to let others interfere with my films," the 28-year-old Dalton native said. 
"Plus, doing sequels is really an artistic dead end because the producers want 
you to continue to emulate the previous films. 
</P>
<P>
"The next film that I'm doing will have as little interference as possible from 
other sources," Burr said during a recent visit. 
</P>
</TEXT>
