<P>
UCLA SHUTS OUT HAWAII 7-0 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
HONOLULU 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
John Sutherland, Scott Schanz and Dave Zancanaro combined to pitch a 
seven-hitter as UCLA blanked Hawaii 7-0 in the finale of a three-game, 
non-conference baseball series Sunday night. 
</P>
<P>
Mannie Adams had three of the Bruins' 13 hits, scored three runs and hit a solo 
home run in the fourth inning to give UCLA a 2-0 lead. 
</P>
<P>
David Tokhelm and David Ravitz each cracked two doubles as the Bruins pounded 
out seven extra base hits. 
</P>
<P>
The Bruins also turned three double plays to blunt any Hawaii rallies. 
</P>
